OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Roy Hayward
OL,5,F"On this particular morning we were in
OL,6,Fa lane and an infantry sergeant
OL,7,Fapproached us and said he was being
OL,8,Fheld up by something, probably a tank
OL,9,Fso we took him on board to show us
OL,10,Fwhere he was having the problem.
OL,12,F"We moved down the lane and suddenly
OL,13,Fthere was a very large thud at the
OL,14,Ffront of our tank and we tried to
OL,15,Freverse and get out of trouble.
OL,17,F"But another shell arrived and this
OL,18,Ftime it penetrated and landed round
OL,19,Fand about my feet and there was an
OL,20,Fexplosion.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
