OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Roy Hayward
OL,5,F"It became absolutely essential that
OL,6,Feverybody got out of the tank.
OL,8,F"The crew all left alright but the
OL,9,Fsergeant obviously didn't know what
OL,10,Fwas happening and before I could get
OL,11,Fout I had to get him out of the
OL,12,Fcockpit and I then managed to crawl
OL,13,Faway from the tank which was beginning
OL,14,Fto get a bit hot.
OL,16,F"In the time I was getting out I had
OL,17,Freceived burns to my right hand and I
OL,18,Fsaw my right leg was completely
OL,19,Fsmashed below the knee and I had lost
OL,20,Fthe front of my left foot.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
