OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Roy Hayward
OL,5,F"I found subsequently there was enough
OL,6,Fheel on that foot to enable me to
OL,7,Fstand otherwise I would not have got
OL,8,Fout of that tank.
OL,10,F"Saved my life, yes. Within a minute
OL,11,For two I would have been burnt to
OL,12,Fdeath."
OL,14,FAfter being taken to a field hospital
OL,15,FMy Hayward was returned to Portsmouth
OL,16,Fwhere both legs were amputated. He has
OL,17,Fbeen through eight pairs of artificial
OL,18,Flimbs in the decades since the
OL,19,Fexplosion.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
